  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "It's completely normal to feel nervous about expressing your feelings, but there are several approaches you can take to let her know you like her:\n\n1. **Build a Friendship**: If you haven\u2019t already, try to build a stronger friendship with her. Spend time together in group settings or engage in shared interests. This can create a more comfortable atmosphere for both of you.\n\n2. **Get to Know Her**: Take time to learn about her interests and hobbies. Find common ground and use that as a starting point to have conversations.\n\n3. **Be Observant**: Pay attention to her reactions and body language. If she seems to enjoy your company and reciprocates interest, it might be a good sign.\n\n4. **Casual Compliments**: Start with casual compliments about things you genuinely appreciate about her, like her sense of style, her sense of humor, or her skills.\n\n5. **Flirt a Little**: Once you're comfortable, use light-hearted flirting to gauge her interest. This can include playful teasing or subtle compliments.\n\n6. **Choose the Right Moment**: Find a moment when you\u2019re both relaxed and can talk privately. Avoid high-pressure situations.\n\n7. **Be Honest but Casual**: When you feel ready, you could say something like, \"I really enjoy spending time with you, and I\u2019ve developed feelings for you.\" Keeping it light and honest can ease the pressure.\n\n8. **Prepare for Any Response**: Be ready for her reaction, whether it\u2019s positive or not. Whatever her response, respect her feelings and be gracious.\n\n9. **Be Yourself**: Authenticity is attractive. Just be genuine in your conversations and interactions.\n\n10. **Practice Makes Perfect**: If you feel very anxious, consider practicing what you want to say with a close friend. This can help you feel more confident.\n\nRemember, you have nothing to lose by being honest, and regardless of the outcome, expressing your feelings can be a positive experience. Good luck!",
